=======================
Operating system README
=======================

The idea of this project is to do a OS with basic stuff.

========
BUILDING
========

1. You will need lib GNUEFI from
https://github.com/ncroxon/gnu-efi?tab=readme-ov-file
as you donwload it you will need to compile it.
I suggest to compile it in VM and copy files on your local computer
Also you will need to manual compile file crt0-efi-x86_64.c
the instruction to compile it is in makefiles/lib_crt0/crt0-efi-x86_64_Makefile

the structure of folder lib should looks like that:

-lib
    -compiled_gnuefi << folder with only compiled gnuefi files from Makefile in GNUEFI
    -gnuefi_source << folder of raw copy from github without compiling
    -manual_compiled_files_gnuefi << folder with files like

crt0-efi-x86_64.o << from own compile
libgnuefi.a << from compiled folder
reloc_x86_64.o << from compiled folder

========
========

2. Make folder build in project folder
and open a termianl in project folder and tap "make".

The compilation process should begin

you will be ask for sudo password because the tools
mkfs.fat and mmd needs a root permision to work with .img files

3. If the compilation process end up with succed
you will have in build folder file "efiboot.img"

efiboot.img is containing
- bootloader for UEFI standard
- kernel thats work with only this bootloader

=======
TESTING
=======

I suggest to use qemu with UEFI.

recommended command form qemu on debian:

.. code-block:: shell

   /home/xxx/directory_to_qemu_folder/qemu-system-x86_64 \
  -M pc \
  -m 2G \
  -smp 3 \
  -cpu qemu64 \
  -net none \
  -drive if=pflash,format=raw,readonly=on,file=./OVMF_CODE.fd \
  -drive if=pflash,format=raw,file=./OVMF_VARS.fd \
  -drive file=./efiboot.img,format=raw \
  -boot d \
  -display gtk \
  -monitor tcp:127.0.0.1:4444,server,nowait \
  -serial stdio \

==================
SUPORTED PLATFORMS
==================

Makefile support at this moment compilation on debian 12.
Any other OS that is compatibile with tis OS should be working.

At this moment i don't support compilation on windows and
virtualizing efiboot.img on virtualbox
